WEBVTT

1
00:00:14.681 --> 00:00:16.224
Hi, I'm Maya.

2
00:00:16.224 --> 00:00:19.227
I'm the vice president of strategy,
operations and outreach

3
00:00:19.269 --> 00:00:20.979
at Google Research.

4
00:00:20.979 --> 00:00:22.272
This means I spend my time

5
00:00:22.272 --> 00:00:25.316
exploring what's on the horizon
and helping to make it real.

6
00:00:26.109 --> 00:00:30.655
That includes AI. You’re probably already using
AI yourself, even if you don't know it.

7
00:00:31.072 --> 00:00:34.534
It's the technology behind things
like giving you optimized traffic routes

8
00:00:34.617 --> 00:00:37.620
or personalized suggestions
for YouTube videos.

9
00:00:37.620 --> 00:00:40.749
AI is also creating new ways of working
or running a business,

10
00:00:41.291 --> 00:00:44.294
and it has a lot of huge potential
for you and your team.

11
00:00:44.961 --> 00:00:46.588
And like any new technology,

12
00:00:46.588 --> 00:00:49.799
it can be intimidating
to know where to start or how to keep up,

13
00:00:50.216 --> 00:00:53.511
especially when it feels like
there are new things happening every day.

14
00:00:54.345 --> 00:00:55.555
Don't worry though.

15
00:00:55.555 --> 00:00:57.057
We're here to help.

16
00:00:57.057 --> 00:01:00.477
In this course, you'll get AI skills
employers are looking for.

17
00:01:00.643 --> 00:01:05.315
This includes important fundamentals
about AI, how to apply AI to your own work,

18
00:01:05.482 --> 00:01:08.485
and how to be a responsible AI user.

19
00:01:08.526 --> 00:01:10.445
These skills will help expand
the possibilities

20
00:01:10.445 --> 00:01:12.697
of what you can do with AI at work.

21
00:01:12.697 --> 00:01:16.451
We brought in a team of AI experts
and practitioners from across

22
00:01:16.451 --> 00:01:18.286
Google to serve as your guides.

23
00:01:18.286 --> 00:01:21.372
You'll explore different use cases
that you can apply to your own work.

24
00:01:22.165 --> 00:01:24.876
We focus on getting you
right into the tools.

25
00:01:24.876 --> 00:01:26.127
That's intentional.

26
00:01:26.127 --> 00:01:28.755
You will learn how to play the piano
without touching the keys. Would you?

27
00:01:29.714 --> 00:01:30.840
AI is no different.

28
00:01:30.840 --> 00:01:33.676
The best way to learn is by doing.

29
00:01:33.676 --> 00:01:36.096
Throughout your learning journey,
you'll practice using

30
00:01:36.096 --> 00:01:39.182
AI with access to Google's most capable
models.

31
00:01:39.682 --> 00:01:41.976
You'll start with the Gemini app
as your home base.

32
00:01:41.976 --> 00:01:44.979
You can think of it as your all purpose
AI assistant.

33
00:01:45.063 --> 00:01:48.066
You can access it from desktop
or on a mobile,

34
00:01:48.441 --> 00:01:50.902
and there's all sorts of stuff
you could do from this one app.

35
00:01:50.902 --> 00:01:55.782
You'll also practice using other
AI tools like NotebookLM and AI Studio.

36
00:01:56.616 --> 00:01:59.619
What are some of the things you'll be able
to do after completing this certificate?

37
00:02:00.203 --> 00:02:03.373
You'll learn how to look ahead
and anticipate questions someone might ask

38
00:02:03.373 --> 00:02:06.918
before a big meeting, or how to understand
a topic that's new to you.

39
00:02:07.377 --> 00:02:11.965
We'll show you how. You'll build project
roadmaps, a compelling presentation,

40
00:02:12.298 --> 00:02:15.301
marketing imagery, and charts
that tell a story.

41
00:02:15.468 --> 00:02:19.389
You'll see how AI can help
turn rough ideas into clear communication

42
00:02:19.389 --> 00:02:23.351
to get your teammates on board,
and you'll be able to transform raw data

43
00:02:23.351 --> 00:02:26.354
into visuals
that everyone on your team can understand.

44
00:02:27.397 --> 00:02:30.817
By the end, you'll even be able to build
your own custom apps

45
00:02:30.984 --> 00:02:34.112
like an interactive dashboard
or a media asset creator,

46
00:02:34.696 --> 00:02:38.116
and you'll do it
by directing AI with natural language.

47
00:02:38.283 --> 00:02:40.243
No coding required.

48
00:02:40.243 --> 00:02:43.246
When you start applying your new
AI skills to your day to day work,

49
00:02:43.329 --> 00:02:46.791
you'll be able to solve new problems
and boost your impact.

50
00:02:47.333 --> 00:02:50.295
After you're done,
you'll earn a certificate from Google

51
00:02:50.295 --> 00:02:52.881
demonstrating skills
that employers are looking for,

52
00:02:52.881 --> 00:02:56.092
and you can add this credential
to your resume and LinkedIn profile.

53
00:02:56.801 --> 00:03:01.514
You'll also have a portfolio of things
you've built yourself using AI.

54
00:03:02.056 --> 00:03:03.683
So let's get started.